cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.LG 

The paper discusses the implementation of bibliometric assessment at the individual level, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely categories as they deal with bibliometrics and publication strategies. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also relevant as it discusses the impact of bibliometrics on researchers and their publication strategies. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are less likely but still possible as they may involve bibliometric analysis and evaluation of research output.
